step1: (host) prepare server hosting binary and configs for genesis version
step2: (3 vms) run_node.sh on the 3 vms

# wait until 2 or 3 eras are passed
step3: (1 vm) get state_root_hash of last switch block and stop 3 nodes.
step4: 1) (1 vm )compress lmdb to tar and transfer
  2) (3 new vms) sftp to get tar of lmdb

step5: (1 vm) generate global_state.toml with state_root_hash and lmdb
step6:
  - 1) (host) transfer global_state.toml to host
  - 2) (host) prepare upgrade configs and change protocol_versions to upgrade version only
  - global_state.toml: to the configs
  - chainspec.toml: (activation_point and version)
  - config.toml: known_addresses
  - protocol_versions: upgrade version only

step7: (3 new vms) upgrade_node to get the upgrade version and start
